public interface  Predicate
     extends java.io.Serializable

     public abstract boolean predicate(Object);
}

Interface for objects that act as predicate functions. For example, if you want to find an object in a Set that fits a certain condition, then write a (anonymous?) class that implements predicate and use it in Set.findSuchThat().
